        </context-group>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit xml:space="preserve" id="08f6b46ea2b21686" weblate-flags="md-text, safe-html, strict-same">
        <source>Basilisk venom is so potent that even creatures that are immune to poison can still be harmed by it, taking 5 points of Speed damage instead of moving down the damage track. (A creature that is immune to poison and acid is fully immune to the venom.)</source>
        <target></target>
        <context-group name="" purpose="location">
